During a press briefing aboard Air Force One en route to Anchorage, Alaska, National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan provided an overview of President Biden's upcoming trip to Hiroshima, Japan, for the G7 Summit. Sullivan highlighted several key topics that will be discussed at the summit, including the war in Ukraine, supply chains and clean energy, the policies and practices of China, economic security, and artificial intelligence. He also addressed questions about the President's decision to cut the trip short and return to Washington, D.C., to focus on negotiations over the budget and the debt ceiling. Sullivan emphasized that the President's presence at the G7 Summit is crucial for building alignment and convergence among key countries and that the trip could be rescheduled at a later date.